                                <lb/>without exception, and makes it clear that 
                                <lb/>there is no separation between the study of language 
                                <lb/>in general and the study of languages, 
                                <lb/>or of a given language or family of languages. But it also means 
                                <lb/>that each division and subdivision of language represents a
                                <lb/>new piece of data, which is as interesting as 
                                <lb/>any other as far as the universal phenomenon of language is concerned.                                
                            </ab>
                            <ab xml:id="en_91Aaaa032" corresp="#pericope_91Aaaa032" xml:lang="en">
